ting institutional aid  and then comparing it to the average salary of a graduate within five years  as reported by Payscale com  Liberal arts schools are classified as those that award more than half of their degrees in the liberal arts  Money magazine also ranked VMI 18th out of the 665 colleges and universities listed in a new national best colleges ranking  and fourth in the liberal arts category  higher than any other liberal arts college in the state  as previously reported  In addition to those rankings  VMI s Department of International Relations and Political Science has been named as one of the best values in the nation in the category of international relations and national security  as reported by College Factual  an independent college rankings organization  VMI was ranked eighth in that category  just behind Stanford University  To calculate its rankings  College Factual uses a variety of factors  among them the average starting and mid career salary of a graduate  whether or not a department is accredited by an outside agency  and the overall ranking of the institution as a whole by College Factual  Overall  College Factual ranked VMI s international relations department 18th in the nation in the category of international relations and national security  just behind Brown University and ahead of George Mason University  The College Factual rankings were recently reported in USA Today  Earlier this month  U S  News and World Report ranked the Institute fourth in the nation among public liberal arts colleges  behind the U S  Naval Academy  the U S  Military Academy  and the U S  Air Force Academy   VMI  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appr